SIMPLE: wisp
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wisp
<hw>Wisp</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>wisp</ets>,
<ets>wips</ets>; probably akin to D. & G. <ets>wisch</ets>, Icel.
<ets>visk</ets>, and perhaps to L. <ets>virga</ets> a twig, rod. Cf.
<er>Verge</er> a rod, <er>Whisk</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A small bundle, as of straw or other like
substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In a small basket, on a <qex>wisp</qex> of hay.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A whisk, or small broom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A Will-o'-the-wisp; an ignis fatuus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>wisp</qex> that flickers where no foot can tread.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wisp</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wisp
<hw>Wisp</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Wisped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Wisping</conjf>.]</vmorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To brush or dress, an with a wisp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To rumple.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wispen</ent>⟦br⟧
